cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.SY 

This paper deals with interference management in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Signal Processing (cs.SI), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper proposes a new approach that combines the principles of treating interference as noise (TIN) and topological interference management (TIM), which are relevant to all of these sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on the technical aspects of wireless network design and optimization, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant because they deal with related topics such as signal processing, multimedia communication, and control systems.
